  (paper "A3")
  (title_block
    (title "V-Cortex - Perifericos: GNSS, MicroSD, Expansao")
    (rev "v1.1")
    (company "V-Cortex")
    (comment 1 "Stage 5: NEO-M9N GNSS 10Hz + U.FL + Bias-T + supercap + PPS | Stage 6: MicroSD SPI + ESD + I2C")
    (comment 2 "NOVO: GNSS_PPS (GPIO35 via 100Ohm), Bias-T antena ativa (L_BIAS+C_BLOCK), decoupling completo")
    (comment 3 "MicroSD: GPIO4=CS, GPIO13=MOSI, GPIO14=CLK, GPIO23=MISO (guia secao 4.4.2)")
  )

  (lib_symbols)

  ;; ============================================================
  ;; BLOCO 1: GNSS NEO-M9N-00B + CIRCUITO COMPLETO
  ;; ============================================================
  (text "U_GNSS — u-blox NEO-M9N-00B\nMPN: NEO-M9N-00B | Sourcing: JLCPCB Global Sourcing ou consignment\nNAO disponivel na LCSC catalogo normal\nPackage: LGA-24 (6.0 x 6.0 x 1.0mm)\n\nALIMENTACAO:\n  VCC: +3.3V (modulo tem regulador interno; NEO-M9N-00B opera com VCC=3.3V)\n  VCC_IO: +3.3V (nivel logico das interfaces UART/I2C/SPI)\n  V_BCKP: supercap CPX3225A via diodo D_BAT + R_BAT\n\nINTERFACE UART (primaria, usada neste projeto):\n  UART_TX (NEO pino 5) -> GPIO16 ESP32 (GNSS_RX) @ 115200 baud\n  UART_RX (NEO pino 6) <- GPIO17 ESP32 (GNSS_TX) @ 115200 baud\n  Inicializacao 10Hz: ver Engineering Guide secao 3.3.4\n\nPPS — Pulse Per Second (GPIO35 ESP32):\n  TIMEPULSE (NEO pino 20) -> R_PPS(100Ohm) -> GPIO35 ESP32\n  R_PPS protege GPIO35 contra ESD e limita corrente de pico\n  GPIO35 e input-only, sem pull interno (nao ha conflito)\n  Firmware: usar iTOW do NAV-PVT para timestamp (mais simples que PPS a 10Hz)\n  Para habilitar PPS a 10Hz: configurar UBX-CFG-TP5 (ver guia secao 3.3.4)\n\nDECOUPLING GNSS (completo, conforme Engineering Guide secao 3.3.2):\n  +3V3 -> [FB_GNSS 600Ohm] -> V_GNSS_VCC\n  V_GNSS_VCC -> C_GNSS_BULK(10uF) -> GND  (bulk, < 5mm do VCC)\n  V_GNSS_VCC -> C_GNSS_100N(100nF) -> GND (bypass, < 0.5mm do pino VCC)\n  V_GNSS_VCC -> C_GNSS_10N(10nF)  -> GND  (alta freq, < 0.5mm do pino VCC_IO)\n\n  COMPONENTES:\n  FB_GNSS:      BLM21PG601SN1D (LCSC: C21179) — ferrite 600Ohm@100MHz\n  C_GNSS_BULK:  10uF X5R 0805 (LCSC: C96446) — NOVO, era ausente\n  C_GNSS_100N:  100nF X7R 0402 (LCSC: C14663) — bypass VCC\n  C_GNSS_10N:   10nF X7R 0402 (LCSC: C15849) — NOVO, bypass VCC_IO alta freq"
    (at 20 20)
    (effects (font (size 1.5 1.5)) (justify left top))
    (uuid "15000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000001")
  )

  ;; ============================================================
  ;; BIAS-T PARA ANTENA ATIVA (NOVO — ERA AUSENTE)
  ;; Engineering Guide secao 3.3.5
  ;; ============================================================
  (text "BIAS-T — ALIMENTACAO ANTENA ATIVA GNSS\n(Engineering Guide secao 3.3.5 — era ausente, NOVO)\n\nFUNCAO: fornece tensao DC (V_ANT) ao cabo coaxial para alimentar o LNA\nda antena patch ativa via o mesmo cabo RF (sem fio extra)\n\nCIRCUITO:\n  V_GNSS_VCC (3.3V) ──[L_BIAS 47nH]──┬── RF+DC (ao conector U.FL)\n                                       │\n                                   [C_BLOCK 100pF]── RF_IN do NEO-M9N\n\nOu equivalente com T-junction:\n  NEO-M9N RF_IN ──[C_BLOCK 100pF]──[ponto RF]──[trilha 50Ohm]── U.FL\n                                        │\n                                    [L_BIAS 47nH]\n                                        │\n                                     V_ANT (3.3V via FB_ANT)\n\nNOTA: O NEO-M9N possui controle de corrente de antena integrado\ne protecao contra curto-circuito no pino V_ANT\nMonitor de tensao de antena: verificar registros UBX-MON-RF\n\nCOMPONENTES:\n  L_BIAS:  47nH indutor RF (LCSC: buscar 47nH 0402 para RF, ex C71851 ou similar)\n           Alternativa: Wurth 744777047A (47nH/300mA 0402)\n  C_BLOCK: 100pF NP0 0402 (LCSC: C14858 ou C1600) — capacitor DC-block\n           NP0/C0G obrigatorio (estabilidade de capacitancia em RF)\n  FB_ANT:  ferrite ou indutor serie na alimentacao V_ANT (opcional, 600Ohm@100MHz)\n\nSE ANTENA PASSIVA (patch sem LNA): omitir L_BIAS e C_BLOCK,\n  conectar NEO-M9N RF_IN diretamente a trilha 50Ohm ao U.FL"
    (at 20 300)
    (effects (font (size 1.5 1.5)) (justify left top))
    (uuid "15000002-0000-0000-0000-000000000001")
  )

  ;; ============================================================
  ;; SUPERCAP BACKUP GNSS
  ;; ============================================================
  (text "BAT1 — Supercap 0.1F/5.5V (Backup GNSS RTC)\n\nCIRCUITO:\n  +3V3 -> [D_BAT Schottky] -> [R_BAT 100Ohm] -> BAT1(0.1F/5.5V) -> GND\n                     │\n  V_BCKP NEO-M9N <───┘ (pino 14)\n\nD_BAT: 1N5819WS SOD-323 (LCSC: C8681 Vishay)\n  Schottky 1A/40V, Vf~0.3V @ baixa corrente\n  Limita V_BCKP a ~3.0V (3.3 - 0.3V) — adequado para supercap 5.5V\n  Impede descarga do supercap de volta para o +3V3 quando desligado\n\nR_BAT: 100Ohm 0402 (LCSC: C104)\n  Limita corrente de carga pico quando supercap esta descarregado\n  Tempo de carga: tau = R_BAT * C_BAT = 100 * 0.1 = 10 segundos (63% carga)\n\nBAT1: 0.1F/5.5V SMD 3.2x2.5mm\n  Seiko CPX3225A ou equivalente\n  LCSC: buscar 'supercap 0.1F 5.5V SMD 3225'\n  Alternativas: VEC3R3225C105Q, CS3216-5R5-105\n  Se indisponivel: usar R_BAT=100k (backup nao funciona, mas circuito opera normalmente)\n  O cold-start sera mais lento (~30s), hot-start ainda funciona se GNSS nunca desligar"
    (at 20 560)
    (effects (font (size 1.5 1.5)) (justify left top))
    (uuid "15000003-0000-0000-0000-000000000001")
  )

  ;; ============================================================
  ;; U.FL CONECTOR + TRILHA RF 50 OHM
  ;; ============================================================
  (text "J_ANT — Conector U.FL / IPEX SMD\nLCSC: C381116 (U.FL-R-SMT-1 Hirose) ou C7501685\n\nTRILHA RF 50 OHM (CRITICA — ver LAYOUT_GUIDE.md):\n  NEO-M9N RF_IN -> [C_BLOCK 100pF] -> [trilha 0.34mm] -> J_ANT U.FL\n  OU (se antena passiva): NEO-M9N RF_IN -> [trilha 0.34mm direto] -> J_ANT U.FL\n\n  Largura trilha: 0.34mm (50Ohm, stackup JLC04161H-7628, L1 ref GND L2, h~0.21mm)\n  Comprimento: < 10mm (Engineering Guide: 'max 15mm sem match de impedancia')\n  Sem vias, sem 90 graus, clearance 1.0mm de outros sinais\n  Remover copper fill e copper pour na regiao da trilha RF"
    (at 600 20)
    (effects (font (size 1.5 1.5)) (justify left top))
    (uuid "15000004-0000-0000-0000-000000000001")
  )

  ;; ============================================================
  ;; MICROSD — GPIO MAPPING CORRIGIDO
  ;; GPIO4=CS, GPIO13=MOSI, GPIO14=CLK, GPIO23=MISO
  ;; ============================================================
  (text "J_SD — Slot MicroSD Push-Push SMD\nLCSC: C780928 (XKB) ou C91145 ou C913631\nTipo: horizontal, push-push eject, SMD\n\nPINAGEM SD em MODO SPI (GPIOs conforme Engineering Guide secao 2.2 e 4.4.2):\n  pino 1 (CS/DAT3):   SD_CS    <- GPIO4  ESP32 (pull-up R_SD_CS 10k -> +3V3)\n  pino 2 (CMD/MOSI):  SD_MOSI  <- GPIO13 ESP32\n  pino 3 (VSS):       GND\n  pino 4 (VDD):       +3V3 via C_SD_BULK\n  pino 5 (CLK):       SD_CLK   <- GPIO14 ESP32\n  pino 6 (VSS):       GND\n  pino 7 (DAT0/MISO): SD_MISO  -> GPIO23 ESP32\n  pino 8 (DAT1):      NC\n  pino 9 (DAT2):      NC\n  CD (card detect):   GPIO livre ou NC\n\nNOTA: GPIO13=MOSI e GPIO14=CLK sao os pinos do HSPI do ESP32\n  O ESP32 pode mapear SPI para qualquer GPIO via GPIO matrix (software SPI)\n  Ou usar HSPI nativo: CLK=GPIO14, MOSI=GPIO13, MISO=GPIO12 (problema: GPIO12 tem pull-down!)\n  SOLUCAO: usar VSPI com remapping via GPIO matrix\n    gpio_config VSPI: CLK=GPIO14, MOSI=GPIO13, MISO=GPIO23, CS=GPIO4\n    O ESP32 IDF permite qualquer GPIO para SPI via spi_bus_config_t\n\nDECOUPLING MicroSD:\n  C_SD_BULK: 10uF X5R 0805 (LCSC: C96446) — bulk VDD\n  C_SD_BYP:  100nF X7R 0402 (LCSC: C14663) — bypass VDD\n  R_SD_CS:   10k 0402 (LCSC: C25741) — pull-up CS -> +3V3 (sem SD ou idle)"
    (at 600 150)
    (effects (font (size 1.5 1.5)) (justify left top))
    (uuid "15000005-0000-0000-0000-000000000001")
  )

  ;; ============================================================
  ;; ESD + EXPANSAO I2C/GPIO
  ;; ============================================================
  (text "ESD PROTECAO HEADERS DE EXPANSAO:\n\nESD1, ESD2 — PRTR5V0U2X (LCSC: C53446675 NXP)\n  2 canais ESD por pacote SOT-363\n  Clamp 5.5V, capacitancia 0.5pF\n\nHEADER I2C J_I2C (conforme Engineering Guide secao 4.4.1):\n  Pin 1: GND\n  Pin 2: +3V3\n  Pin 3: SDA (GPIO21) — via ESD1, pull-up R_I2C_SDA(4.7k) -> +3V3\n  Pin 4: SCL (GPIO22) — via ESD1, pull-up R_I2C_SCL(4.7k) -> +3V3\n\nHEADER SPI J_SPI (Engineering Guide secao 4.4.2):\n  Pin 1: GND\n  Pin 2: +3V3\n  Pin 3: MOSI (GPIO13)\n  Pin 4: MISO (GPIO23)\n  Pin 5: SCK  (GPIO14)\n  Pin 6: CS_EXP (GPIO27)\n\nHEADER GPIO J_GPIO (Engineering Guide secao 4.4.3):\n  Pin 1: GND\n  Pin 2: +3V3\n  Pin 3: GPIO26 (via ESD2)\n  Pin 4: GPIO32 (via ESD2)\n  Pin 5: GPIO36/VP — ADC input (NTC temperatura)\n  Pin 6: GPIO39/VN — ADC input expansao\n\nNOTA: GPIO26, GPIO32 ficam livres para expansao futura\nNOTA: GPIO36 e GPIO39 sao input-only, sem pull interno"
    (at 600 470)
    (effects (font (size 1.5 1.5)) (justify left top))
    (uuid "15000006-0000-0000-0000-000000000001")
  )

  ;; ============================================================
  ;; RESUMO BOM — STAGES 5 e 6
  ;; ============================================================
  (text "RESUMO BOM — STAGE 5 (GNSS) e STAGE 6 (Perifericos)\n\nREF           VALUE           LCSC          NOTAS\nU_GNSS        NEO-M9N-00B     GLOBAL_SRC    LGA-24, Global Sourcing ou consignment\nFB_GNSS       BLM21PG601SN1   C21179        Ferrite 600Ohm GNSS VCC\nC_GNSS_BULK   10uF X5R        C96446        NOVO — bulk GNSS VCC\nC_GNSS_100N   100nF X7R       C14663        Bypass GNSS VCC\nC_GNSS_10N    10nF X7R NP0    C15849        NOVO — bypass alta freq GNSS VCC_IO\nL_BIAS        47nH RF         (verificar)   NOVO — Bias-T antena ativa\nC_BLOCK       100pF NP0       C14858        NOVO — DC-block antena RF\nR_PPS         100Ohm          C104          NOVO — serie GNSS PPS -> GPIO35\nJ_ANT         U.FL            C381116       Conector antena externa\nD_BAT         1N5819WS        C8681         Schottky carga supercap\nR_BAT         100Ohm          C104          Limite corrente carga supercap\nBAT1          0.1F/5.5V SMD   (verificar)   Supercap backup GNSS — buscar LCSC\nJ_SD          MicroSD push    C780928       Slot MicroSD SMD\nC_SD_BULK     10uF X5R        C96446        Bulk VDD SD\nC_SD_BYP      100nF X7R       C14663        Bypass VDD SD\nR_SD_CS       10k             C25741        Pull-up SD_CS (GPIO4)\nESD1          PRTR5V0U2X      C53446675     ESD 2 canais expansao 1\nESD2          PRTR5V0U2X      C53446675     ESD 2 canais expansao 2\nNTC1          10k B3950       C4004475      NTC temperatura (GPIO36)\nR_NTC         10k             C25741        Pull-up NTC -> +3V3\nC_NTC         100nF           C14663        Filtro NTC ADC\nR_I2C_SDA     4.7k            C25900        Pull-up SDA GPIO21\nR_I2C_SCL     4.7k            C25900        Pull-up SCL GPIO22"
    (at 20 780)
    (effects (font (size 1.5 1.5)) (justify left top))
    (uuid "15000007-0000-0000-0000-000000000001")
  )

